Doom Emacs Configuration
========================

This is a personal Doom Emacs configuration.  This file describes what
must be installed on a new machine before this configuration can be
used.  The instructions below assume macOS with Homebrew, since the
configuration adds /opt/homebrew/bin to `exec-path'; adjust package
names for other systems as needed.

Contents
--------

  init.el          Enabled Doom modules.
  config.el        Personal settings, key bindings, eglot servers.
  packages.el      Extra packages installed on top of Doom.
  local-packages/  Personal packages, tracked as git submodules:
                     translate.el          (github.com/desonglll/translate.el)
                     kill-other-buffers.el (github.com/desonglll/kill-other-buffers.el)

Requirements
------------

1. Core

   * GNU Emacs 29.1 or later (30+ recommended), built with tree-sitter
     support.  On macOS:

       brew install emacs-plus@30    # from d12frosted/emacs-plus tap

   * git 2.23 or later
   * ripgrep (rg)  -- required by Doom for searching
   * fd            -- faster file finding; bound to M-# (consult-fd)
   * GNU coreutils and make

       brew install git ripgrep fd coreutils make

2. Fonts

   * Iosevka Term SS15 -- primary font set in config.el

       brew install --cask font-iosevka-term-ss15

   * Nerd Fonts icons for the mode line and dashboard; after the first
     start run inside Emacs:

       M-x nerd-icons-install-fonts

3. PDF support (:tools pdf)

   pdf-tools compiles a small server (epdfinfo) on first run and needs:

       brew install poppler automake pkg-config

4. Language toolchains and LSP servers

   LSP is provided through eglot.  Install the servers for the
   languages you actually use; the rest can be skipped.

   Language     Toolchain            Language server
   --------     ---------            ---------------
   C / C++      clang                clangd (ships with Xcode CLT)
   Elixir       elixir               elixir-ls, unpacked to
                                     ~/elixir-ls-v0.31.1/ (path is
                                     hard-coded in config.el)
   Go           go                   gopls
   JavaScript   node                 typescript-language-server
   LaTeX        MacTeX or TeX Live   texlab (optional)
   Lua          lua                  lua-language-server (optional)
   Nix          nix                  nil or nixd
   Python       python3              ty (config.el registers "ty server"
                                     with eglot); pyright as fallback
   Ruby/Rails   ruby                 ruby-lsp (gem install ruby-lsp)
   Rust         rustup               rust-analyzer (rustup component)
   Shell        bash/zsh             bash-language-server, shellcheck
   Swift        Xcode                sourcekit-lsp (ships with Xcode)
   Zig          zig                  zls (optional)

   Note that config.el also adds ~/.local/bin to `exec-path', so
   servers installed there (e.g. via pipx or uv) are found.

5. Miscellaneous tools

   * just   -- for just-mode        (brew install just)
   * typst  -- for typst-ts-mode    (brew install typst)
   * protoc -- for protobuf-mode    (brew install protobuf)
   * An API key for gptel, if you use it (e.g. OPENAI_API_KEY or an
     Anthropic key, configured separately).

Installation
------------

1. Install Doom Emacs:

       git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/doomemacs/doomemacs \
           ~/.config/emacs

2. Clone this repository WITH submodules (the local packages are
   required by packages.el; note the submodule URLs use SSH, so a
   GitHub SSH key must be set up first):

       git clone --recurse-submodules \
           git@github.com:desonglll/doom.git ~/.config/doom

   If already cloned without submodules:

       git -C ~/.config/doom submodule update --init

3. Run the installer and sync:

       ~/.config/emacs/bin/doom install
       ~/.config/emacs/bin/doom sync

   Add ~/.config/emacs/bin to PATH for convenience.

4. Start Emacs, then run `M-x nerd-icons-install-fonts'.  The first
   time a PDF is opened, pdf-tools will offer to build epdfinfo;
   accept it.

5. Check the installation:

       ~/.config/emacs/bin/doom doctor

Notes
-----

* Org files are expected under ~/org/ (see `org-directory').
* Backups and auto-save files go to ~/.emacs.d/backups/.
* The theme is gruber-darker; pyim with pyim-basedict provides Chinese
  input inside Emacs.

Bugs
----

Report problems at https://github.com/desonglll/doom/issues.
